## Summary

The API contract is comprehensive and well-structured. The Rust layer (`pablo-core`) will expose 15+ new async functions covering sessions, preferences, and user endpoints. Swift callers will invoke these via UniFFI, passing `base_url` and `token` at call time (keeping tokens in native Keychain, never in Rust). 

The two critical paths for PABLO-D-108 are:
1. **Session scheduling** — `POST /api/sessions/schedule`, `GET /api/sessions/today`, `PATCH /api/sessions/{id}/status`
2. **Transcript upload** — `POST /api/sessions/{id}/transcript`

All other endpoints (patients, preferences, SOAP notes) are dependencies or secondary features.

